{"path": "/data6/zmf/Wan2.2_SA3_hif4_edges8_fp16_noscale_norowmax_baseline_para01/QK_POLICY_IMPLEMENTATION.md", "kind": "file", "size": 11115, "mtime": 1781175594, "head": "# QK Policy Implementation Notes\n\nThis document records the QK pseudo-quantization policy implementation added for\nWan2.2 custom SDPA inference.\n\n## Goal\n\nThe implementation makes QK^T pseudo-quantization configurable per model phase,\nattention type, and transformer layer. It supports:\n\n- `hif4`: existing HiF4 pseudo-quantized QK path.\n- `nvfp4`: NVFP4 pseudo-quantized QK path.\n- `ref` / `bf16`: direct QK matmul without Q/K pseudo-quantization.\n- JSON policies for per-layer mode selection.\n- Runtime fallback from unstable Hif4 tiles.\n- Optional sampled calibration logs and compare-mode error metrics.\n\n## Changed Files\n\n- `generate.py`\n  - Added CLI arguments for QK mode, policy, fallback, guard, logging, and compare mode.\n  - Calls `configure_qk_policy(...)` at generation startup.\n\n- `wan/text2video.py`\n  - Annotates low/high noise models as `low_noise` and `high_noise`.\n  - Passes `model_role`, `timestep`, `timestep_idx`, and `cond_type` into model forward.\n\n- `wan/modules/model.py`\n  - Passes `quant_context` through `WanModel -> WanAttentionBlock -> WanSelfAttention/WanCrossAttention`.\n  - Adds `layer_idx` using `enumerate(self.blocks)`.\n  - Adds `attn_type` as `self` or `cross`."}
{"path": "/data6/zmf/Wan2.2_SA3_hif4_edges8_fp16_noscale_norowmax_baseline_para01/README_ROWMAX_FULL_CODE_TRANSFER.md", "kind": "file", "size": 971, "mtime": 1781175594, "head": "# Wan2.2 Row-Max Full Code Transfer Bundle\n\nThis archive contains the full `Wan2.2/` source tree with row-max calibration changes, plus the calibration prompt files and `collect_rowmax_fp16.sh` inside `Wan2.2/`.\n\nIt excludes model weights, generated videos, images, row-max profiles, caches, and git metadata.\n\n## Extract\n\nExtract from the parent directory where you want `Wan2.2/` to live:\n\n```bash\ncd /root\ntar -xzf /path/to/Wan2.2_rowmax_full_code_bundle_20260608.tar.gz\n```\n\n## Smoke Test\n\nUse your real checkpoint path:\n\n```bash\ncd /root/Wan2.2\nCKPT_DIR=/root/autodl-tmp/Wan2.2-T2V-A14B LIMIT=1 SAMPLE_STEPS=1 bash collect_rowmax_fp16.sh\n```\n\n## Full Calibration\n\n```bash\ncd /root/Wan2.2\nCKPT_DIR=/root/autodl-tmp/Wan2.2-T2V-A14B bash collect_rowmax_fp16.sh\n```\n\nDefaults: CUDA device 0, `t2v-A14B`, `480*832`, fp16 row-level row max, 1024x1024 blocks, one profile file per prompt, cond/uncond separated, T5 on CPU, model offload enabled, video decode/save skipped.\n"}
{"path": "/data6/zmf/Wan2.2_SA3_hif4_edges8_fp16_noscale_norowmax_baseline_para01/README_ROWMAX_SCALAR_PRESET.md", "kind": "file", "size": 907, "mtime": 1781175594, "head": "# Row-max scalar preset mode\n\nThis Wan2.2 package includes a small text preset file instead of requiring the original large `.pt` row-max profile.\n\nIncluded file:\n\n```bash\nrowmax_scalar_presets_stable_heads_offset_m10.txt\n```\n\nThe text file stores one scalar preset per selected stable head/timestep/branch/attention type:\n\n```text\nbranch attn timestep layer query_len key_len num_heads head preset_max\n```\n\n`preset_max` was generated as:\n\n```text\nmax(profile_row_max[head, :]) - 10\n```\n\nAt inference time:\n\n- heads listed in the txt use the scalar preset and skip runtime max search\n- heads missing from the txt still compute row max dynamically\n- no 16G `.pt` profile is needed\n\nBefore inference:\n\n```bash\nsource ./use_rowmax_stable_heads.sh\n```\n\nThen run your normal Wan `generate.py` command.\n\nCoverage:\n\n```text\n1051 / 1600 layer-heads = 65.6875%\n42040 / 64000 layer-head-timestep slots = 65.6875%\n```\n"}
{"path": "/data6/zmf/Wan2.2_SA3_hif4_edges8_fp16_noscale_norowmax_baseline_para01/README_ROWMAX_TRANSFER.md", "kind": "file", "size": 886, "mtime": 1781175594, "head": "# Wan2.2 Row-Max Calibration Transfer Bundle\n\nThis bundle contains only row-max calibration code and prompt files. It does not contain model weights, generated videos, profiles, or caches.\n\n## Install\n\nExtract at the destination `Wan2.2_zdh` root, where weights already exist:\n\n```bash\ncd /path/to/Wan2.2_zdh\ntar -xzf /path/to/rowmax_calibration_code_bundle_20260608.tar.gz\n```\n\n## Run\n\n```bash\nbash collect_rowmax_fp16.sh\n```\n\nDefaults: `CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=0`, `t2v-A14B`, `VIDEO_SIZE=480*832`, fp16 row-level row max, 1024x1024 blocks, one profile file per prompt, cond/uncond separated, video save/decode skipped.\n\nSmoke test one prompt and one sampling step:\n\n```bash\nLIMIT=1 SAMPLE_STEPS=1 bash collect_rowmax_fp16.sh\n```\n\nIf paths differ:\n\n```bash\nZDH_ROOT=/path/to/Wan2.2_zdh WAN_CODE_DIR=/path/to/Wan2.2_zdh/Wan2.2 CKPT_DIR=/path/to/Wan2.2_zdh bash collect_rowmax_fp16.sh\n```\n"}
